After passing the location several times and seeing a crowd. I stopped in on a Saturday afternoon when it was not too busy.  I wanted to try the salmon burger but was immediately told "No salmon and no shark" followed by silence. There was no attempt to sell any of the other selections by the cashier.  I settled on the 8 oz burger and fries paid and waited. In less than 3 minutes the order was ready which made me a little suspicious. I stepped up to the condiment station and with each selection the girl working there said "Is that it?" Finally I was done and was handed my purchase, said thank you and got no response.  When I arrived at home I popped open the box and was met with limp fries. I grabbed one and tasted. Not good, I could taste the very old oil they had been cooked in. Next with a quick bite of the burger my suspicions were confirmed. The meat was not fresh and having worked in the restaurant industry for a number of years,  I knew the burger had been cooked prior to me placing my order and simply reheated.  I was somewhat unhappy with the service but extremely disappointed in the food. Needless to say I will not be returning to this establishment.
